[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 565 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Mon 6 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-07/07/c_81018.htm


On 6 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 6 Jul 2020):
- 8 new cases of confirmed infections (all were imported cases, 2 in Liaoning province, 2 in Shanghai municipality, 2 in Sichuan province, 1 in Inner Mongolia autonomous region and 1 in Guangdong province), 2 new cases of suspected infections (both were imported cases, 1 in Inner Mongolia and 1 in Shanghai), and no deaths.
- A total of 1942 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 565 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 528 recovered and discharged from hospital; 764 486 close contacts with infected patients, and 3940 are under medical observation.
- 15 new asymptomatic cases (including 14 imported cases); 2 asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 114 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 77 imported cases).
- 1285 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 17 cases since 5 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau, 449 in Taiwan.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The 8 new confirmed cases in the last 24 hours were all imported and no cases were reported from Beijing. The 1st case in Beijing was reported on 11 Jun 2020; as of 6 Jul 2020, there have been 336 cases reported from Beijing, 21 in Hebei, and 6 in Liaoning (2 new cases in last 24 hours), most likely associated with this outbreak. Other provinces including Sichuan Guangdong and Inner Mongolia autonomous region also warrant monitoring.

There were 15 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals and 2 new conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, there have been 36 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infections reported by China.

Hong Kong reported 17 new cases. According to a press release, the newly reported cases announced today [6 Jul 2020] involve 12 males and 5 females aged between 3 and 78. Except for the 1283rd case, all had travel history during the incubation period. The webpage mentions a total 1286 cases [1285 confirmed and one probable case] https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/06/P2020070600681.htm.

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with the SARS-CoV-2; many of whom are detected as asymptomatic at the time of positive PCR testing.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png, and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7549897,155. - Mod.UBA]

