[D] Iran: 243 051 total cases, 11 731 deaths
Date: Mon 6 Jul 2020
Source: Xinhuanet [abridged, edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-07/07/c_139192864.htm


The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Iran rose to 243 051 on Monday [6 Jul 2020]. Meanwhile, Qatar's infections crossed the major threshold of 100 000.

Iran, the hardest-hit country by the COVID-19 pandemic in the Middle East region, reported 2613 new cases, bringing the total number of infections to 243 051. The pandemic has so far claimed the lives of 11 731 Iranians, up by 160 in the past 24 hours. A total of 204 083 coronavirus patients have recovered, with 3201 still in critical condition.

Iran has reintroduced some restrictions to parts of the country amid the resurgence of COVID-19 infections and fatalities, including shutting down libraries for at least one week in the capital Tehran. Sports clubs and complexes, ceremony halls and cinemas in high-risk zones were also closed again for at least one week.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 6 Jul 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran is 243 051, including 11 731 deaths, an increase of 2613 cases and 160 deaths since 5 Jul 2020. The numbers of daily reported cases and deaths are slowing increasing.

Takeaway message: Premature lifting of restrictions is taking its toll in Iran as is elsewhere in the world. Unfortunately, many people think that lifting of restrictions means the virus has gone away and measures like mask wearing and social distancing are no longer necessary leading to resurgences of increased transmission and the resultant increase in severe cases and deaths. And the need to re-implement some forms of lockdown to flatten the curves again so the health systems aren't overwhelmed.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7549897,128. - Mod.UBA]

